ENTRY       EC 1.8.4.10                 Enzyme
NAME        adenylyl-sulfate reductase (thioredoxin);
            thioredoxin-dependent 5'-adenylylsulfate reductase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on a sulfur group of donors;
            With a disulfide as acceptor
SYSNAME     AMP,sulfite:thioredoxin-disulfide oxidoreductase (adenosine-5'-phosphosulfate-forming)
REACTION    AMP + sulfite + thioredoxin disulfide = 5'-adenylyl sulfate + thioredoxin [RN:R07176]
ALL_REAC    R07176
SUBSTRATE   AMP [CPD:C00020];
            sulfite [CPD:C00094];
            thioredoxin disulfide [CPD:C00343]
PRODUCT     5'-adenylyl sulfate [CPD:C00224];
            thioredoxin [CPD:C00342]
COMMENT     Uses adenylyl sulfate, not phosphoadenylyl sulfate, distinguishing this enzyme from EC 1.8.4.8, phosphoadenylyl-sulfate reductase (thioredoxin). Uses thioredoxin as electron donor, not glutathione or other donors, distinguishing it from EC 1.8.4.9 [adenylyl-sulfate reductase (glutathione)] and EC 1.8.99.2 (adenylyl-sulfate reductase).
HISTORY     EC 1.8.4.10 created 2003
